name: treatment of used vegetable cooking oil, purified, esterification | glycerine | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/10835/documentation

This dataset represents the treatment of purified vegetable cooking oil by esterification with methanol to produce methyl ester and glycerine. The transesterification is base-catalysed with sodium methoxide and sodium hydroxide. ;This dataset could be too used for the esterification of waste animal fat into methyl ester and glycerine. The studied plant treats both types of waste. ;Data have been collected for the annual production of the esterification plant and adapted to production of one liter of vegetable oil methyl esther. To fit with the current ecoinvent datasets, collected data have been divided between a purification step and an esterification step.This dataset considers only the esterification step. 

From reception of purified cooking oil and chemicals at factory gate. 

This activity ends at esterification plant with the produced methyl ester and glycerine. 
The dataset includes the esterification process of purified oil into methyl ester and glycerine, the intermediate storage of the oil and products and treatment of specific wastewater effluents.
category: E:Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities/38:Waste collection, treatment and disposal activities; materials recovery/383:Materials recovery/3830:Materials recovery

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Data from 2012, current technology in Quebec.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data from one biodiesel producer in the Quebec region.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Typical waste oil esterification plant designed for methyl ester production (for the vehicle fuels market), Quebec context. Based on industrial data from one biodiesel producer in the Quebec region with a low production volume (2 000 000 litres of biodiesel per year).  The transesterification is base-catalysed with sodium methoxide and sodium hydroxide.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription:
Data from one biodiesel producer used to represent the total Quebec region production.
Energy consumption of the plant has been divided between purification and esterification seps based on industrial expertise.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Industrial data from one biodiesel producer in the Quebec region.
